{"word":"H374 - אֵיפָה - ʼêyphâh - ay-faw' - Ephah","slug":"H374","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֵיפָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼêyphâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ay-faw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Ephah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05E4;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#x05D0;&#x05D9;&#x05E4;&#x05D4; - 'e&#x0302;ypha&#x0302;h  'e&#x0302;pha&#x0302;h</b> - <i>ay-faw', ay-faw'</i><p/>Of Egyptian derivation; an <i>ephah</i> or measure for grain; hence a <i>measure</i> in general: - ephah, (divers) measure (-s)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H369\">H369</a>, <a href=\"#/H371\">H371</a>"}]}